json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage ","message":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.gmail","typeVersion":2.1,"position":[7978,1420],"id":"1adb2875-bb83-4737-b3de-6702f337b78e","name":"Escalate Failure to Gmail","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Conversation Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[8302,1420],"id":"10ff9fbc-3878-41f7-bf99-be8235e4cd17","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf07863-conversation`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Required Fields Present?","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"cdd5a09d-8504-6c2c-fccb-8add53deabf8","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Required Fields Present?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.message }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reason & Act (AI Agent) · ②→ Abort — Malformed Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"18fb84ea-acf8-26fc-a50a-2691a3902747","name":"Note: Required Fields Present?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Abort — Malformed Input\n\nFails fast with a clear message; triggers the error workflow instead of processing bad data.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,1030],"id":"9ac7a15d-79b4-3949-887d-d4ad61a520ea","name":"Note: Abort — Malformed Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reason & Act (AI Agent)\n\nThe AI brain: reads the input, decides which attached tools to call (and in what order), then composes the answer.\n\nPorts: ①→ Shape Agent Output · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"9f384b12-d544-5548-71e2-42945a71ab03","name":"Note: Reason & Act (AI Agent)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenRouter Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenRouter API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"14d4637d-fc8e-ed58-efb8-85259fae5e29","name":"Note: OpenRouter Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Custom Logic Tool\n\nDeterministic code helper the agent can invoke for exact computation.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1510],"id":"aea44c44-ec74-95a0-ea6a-308a95bb9595","name":"Note: Custom Logic Tool"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Think It Through\n\nScratchpad tool: lets the agent reason step-by-step before acting.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[790,1750],"id":"bc7e68f9-111c-5e31-de22-1eefa96a1a32","name":"Note: Think It Through"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Conversation Memory\n\nConversation memory keyed by session — the bot remembers earlier turns for each user separately.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `memory`\n\n🔑 Postgres connection","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[547,1810],"id":"ce73faad-aa3d-0296-96c0-9e5961da5916","name":"Note: Conversation Memory"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Shape Agent Output\n\nShapes the item: writes `answer`, `confidence`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Confident Enough?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1114,520],"id":"e69f1376-2f65-5652-0659-7fda8a8591af","name":"Note: Shape Agent Output"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Confident Enough?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.confidence }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets · ②→ Escalate to Human Queue","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1438,520],"id":"0a699001-c8b7-7917-2d4b-e2473b4a2b2e","name":"Note: Confident Enough?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1762,280],"id":"ecb4321d-d86d-8ea4-87da-04e8e334832a","name":"Note: Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate to Human Queue\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2086,880],"id":"85240d2e-03f9-d74d-ec66-96b1b4a82a91","name":"Note: Escalate to Human Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Join Outcomes\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2734,520],"id":"6806549f-3266-1729-d5b1-51394b026ca9","name":"Note: Join Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3706,520],"id":"f06335eb-402b-8660-ef4f-a56a417a8865","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4030,520],"id":"99b6ee17-3c3a-5893-45a3-718e7102f648","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4354,520],"id":"7a7361b6-d20d-6507-a0b5-fe42dd08e90d","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4678,520],"id":"e1219da0-7a67-57e6-d810-3f7e394ae1b2","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5002,520],"id":"d3364a3f-0dc8-b1f7-3593-f16cbb78fc8b","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5326,520],"id":"2e98c396-f116-7b43-f2ab-0bc0cdc6e653","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5650,520],"id":"1bba623d-6bd7-9de1-54bb-29a99468512f","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Load Previous Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5974,520],"id":"db28beb5-3d16-389e-88a8-f1e221d2a9f0","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6298,520],"id":"5b20be80-d72c-f48f-7f4c-652b0707f7a6","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6622,520],"id":"a71574bf-3998-813d-7089-7903c8c183a9","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per conversation (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6946,520],"id":"9ed3f347-39a6-eb38-f64f-9403fa2002f6","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7270,520],"id":"a477cc41-0f19-a045-fe53-280ab23c71cb","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7594,520],"id":"ab602cf3-e26a-c0d9-5475-352e95cbc3a4","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7918,520],"id":"31df66dd-c7f6-7abd-3a16-22d71f2847dc","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8242,520],"id":"10acbea5-467b-08d2-cd8b-41b328248df6","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Gmail","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7594,1540],"id":"56741f60-81d5-fff1-262f-297867593313","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Gmail\n\ngmail — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7918,1540],"id":"3fb67b8b-d765-b505-ea29-a5a6879b7585","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8242,1540],"id":"d1f52999-e3b8-d474-4eab-42cae252021f","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Power an AI agent task with Gmail for Support Bots\n\n**Pattern:** AI Agent · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nPower an AI agent task with Gmail for Support Bots. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual support bots is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Required Fields Present? → Reason & Act (AI Agent) → Shape Agent Output → Confident Enough? → Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets → Join Outcomes → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai agent without manual effort\n- Anyone automating support bots in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Improves response time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; OpenRouter API key; Postgres connection.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"17101155-7ff0-9248-f15e-507b5b00f98b","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"fc5cbad9-69a6-6d64-7577-3fcb3a0cb1e7","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"d9a2aa79-340c-40ac-1fc8-ee089321e903","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"8d1ecead-c20a-0eb7-915c-3703b9ce7715","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your support bots process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"e8d1bc31-77d2-9f02-1a94-f76c88cfc84b","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Required Fields Present?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Required Fields Present?":{"main":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Abort — Malformed Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenRouter Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Custom Logic Tool":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Think It Through":{"ai_tool":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_tool","index":0}]]},"Conversation Memory":{"ai_memory":[[{"node":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","type":"ai_memory","index":0}]]},"Reason & Act (AI Agent)":{"main":[[{"node":"Shape Agent Output","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Shape Agent Output":{"main":[[{"node":"Confident Enough?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Confident Enough?":{"main":[[{"node":"Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Escalate to Human Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate to Human Queue":{"main":[[{"node":"Join Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Join Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Gmail","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Gmail":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"815229b5-1a7f-41ad-8b4b-4730fcb8bde0","id":"FDX07863"}